entries.meaning: By or across water, especially of travel.
examples: This detailed account of diversification shows that most of New Zealand's biota results from overwater colonization, rather than survival since New Zealand separated from Australia .

entries.meaning: Built or situated on stilts in the ocean.

verbs.description: overwater (third-person singular simple present overwaters, present participle overwatering, simple past and past participle overwatered)
